data.title: What if the Ottomans won the first Balkan War, and how would that affect WW1?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 2): November 1917.

The new (prime minister) "grand vizier" "Talat Pasha" visits the former sultan, Abdulhamid II, under surveillance.

He was on his way to see the man he knocked down 9 years ago. It was actually a bit of "advising" and a bit of "apologizing".
